body.title: Tim Urban: Inside the mind of a master procrastinator | TED
body.description:
Tim Urban knows that procrastination doesn't make sense, but he's never been able to shake his habit of waiting until the last minute to get things done. In this hilarious and insightful talk, Urban takes us on a journey through YouTube binges, Wikipedia rabbit holes and bouts of staring out the window -- and encourages us to think harder about what we're really procrastinating on, before we run out of time.

For more from Tim Urban, visit Wait But Why: http://www.waitbutwhy.com/

body.title: Tim Urban: Inside the mind of a master procrastinator | TED
body.description:
Tim Urban knows that procrastination doesn't make sense, but he's never been able to shake his habit of waiting until the last minute to get things done. In this hilarious and insightful talk, Urban takes us on a journey through YouTube binges, Wikipedia rabbit holes and bouts of staring out the window -- and encourages us to think harder about what we're really procrastinating on, before we run out of time.

For more from Tim Urban, visit Wait But Why: http://www.waitbutwhy.com/

Visit http://TED.com to get our entire library of TED Talks, transcripts, translations, personalized talk recommendations and more.

The TED Talks channel features the best talks and performances from the TED Conference, where the world's leading thinkers and doers give the talk of their lives in 18 minutes (or less). Look for talks on Technology, Entertainment and Design -- plus science, business, global issues, the arts and more. You're welcome to link to or embed these videos, forward them to others and share these ideas with people you know.

meta.title: TED
meta.description:
The TED Talks channel features the best talks and performances from the TED Conference, where the world's leading thinkers and doers give the talk of their lives in 18 minutes (or less). Look for talks on Technology, Entertainment and Design -- plus science, business, global issues, the arts and more. You're welcome to link to or embed these videos, forward them to others and share these ideas with people you know.

TED's videos may be used for non-commercial purposes under a Creative Commons License, Attribution–Non Commercial–No Derivatives (or the CC BY – NC – ND 4.0 International) and in accordance with our TED Talks Usage Policy: https://www.ted.com/about/our-organization/our-policies-terms/ted-talks-usage-policy. For more information on using TED for commercial purposes (e.g. employee learning, in a film or online course), please submit a Media Request at https://media-requests.ted.com

data.content: Head over to the @TEDAudioCollective channel to listen to Conversations With People Who Hate Me featuring @dylanmarron 🥳

originalPost.contentText: Did you know Conversations With People Who Hate Me is now a part of the TED Audio Collective? 🎉 Listen to this podcast hosted by @dylanmarron. Dylan explores what happens when online feuders step out from behind the keyboard and get to know the human on the other side of the screen. In this week's episode, artist Michael James Schneider (@blcksmth on Instagram) speaks about being "Twitter's main character" and how he maneuvers the online hate that he receives for his art.  Listen now at: https://youtu.be/YBchldQuHjg

data.contentText: What is the future of food? Tune in tomorrow Tuesday, March 15 at 12P ET as TED livestreams talks and original series that cover the topics of how we nourish ourselves and the planet. Speakers and experts such as Isha Datar, Dr. Jen Gunter and more will tackle the systems-level design thinking around industry and agriculture as well as new ways to improve individual human health and reduce cruelty to animals. For the full playlist of talks featured, click here: https://www.youtube.com/playlist?list...

In honor of World Wildlife Day, join TED in a livestream event today at 12P ET. This livestream features talks that cover the vast biodiversity on our planet. From a discovery stemming from a king cobra bite to the magnificent sound of fishing cats, TED celebrates wildlife and conservation. For all the talks featured in our livestream, click here: https://www.youtube.com/playlist?list...

In celebration of Black History Month in the US and Canada, TED is spotlighting speakers such as Shonda Rhimes, Swizz Beatz, D.L Stewart, Tarana Burke, and many more. Tune in Friday, February 4 at 11am ET for a livestream of personal storytelling featuring topics such as the freedom of expressing yourself through art, the importance of telling your own story, healthy co-parenting tips, and so much more.  

To watch all the talks included in the Black History Month Spotlight livestream, click here: https://www.youtube.com/playlist?list...

UN Deputy Secretary-General Amina J. Mohammed invites us to reimagine what the journey to net-zero could look like if we invest in people's climate efforts while prioritizing the 17 Sustainable Development Goals -- a blueprint of interlinked global goals to protect humanity and our warming planet. Watch the full talk from the 2021 TED Countdown Summit here: https://youtu.be/uX-0gEOdAuU

Which TED Talks captured the world’s attention this year? Tune in Friday, December 17 at 11am ET for a livestream event of the top 50 most-watched talks on YouTube in 2021. Listen to Amanda Gorman, Esther Perel, Bill Gates and more discuss topics like the secret to forming better habits, thoughts on burnout culture and even figuring out exactly how many glasses of water you need each day.

To watch all 50 talks featured in the livestream, click here: https://www.youtube.com/playlist?list...

data.textDisplay: Costco would sell a lot more large screen 4K TVs  if they had this playing instead of those stupid parrots and lizards.  THIS is why we have 4K tv.
This is a great 4K demo for any 4K TV! It should be shown in stores and it will drastically increase sales!
One of the greatest works of cinematography in existence.

The amount of devices and skills involved in making this is the actual tribute!
From high speed cameras, lenses, lighting, water spraying devices, controlled flames and explosions, trampolines, motorcycles, breast implants, acrobatics, post production, know-how, etc. 
All things, well done!
Once upon a time this was one of the few videos to test 4k, the 1st search result was this master piece

The song is majestic
The cut and composition of the video godly
The girls bouncing around motorcyclist jump + firework + water bubble etc epic idea
This is 15/10

Incredible video from start to finish. Music, footage, everything about the video was perfect. Very well done! Great work to all who helped produce it. I am shocked it doesn't have 50 million views by now.
This needs to win an Oscar.
I still vividly remember the first time I saw your Milky Way Timelapses a decade ago, and you haven't ceased to blow me away since. Always one step ahead and never put out anything but dope shit.
This is incredible! Such Great Art. Good work! It would be nice to see other videos like this one.
You need to make a series of these... I'd pretty much rather watch this than anything I can think of
Brilliant!! I smiled from ear to ear for the whole 4 mins hehe. Also that tune is banging!, and fits perfectly with this, i love it. Great work !
Como quisiera darle like cada que reproduzco este video, esta muy bien echo, felicidades por la producción

Hey Dustin!!! We desperately need more 4k content for our tvs!!!! Please your videos are the pinnacle of 4k and slow motion content!!!!! More!!! I greatly appreciate the thought you put into  your videos. Good fn job!!!!!
The need to come out with a part II 🔥🔥🔥

The slowmo, camera angle and editing are amazing. I know it is probably after the fact, but will you make a video on the making of this? From the hatching of the idea to the set, editing and challenges, etc.

Honesty! The best slow motion I have ever seen in my life. Even the bubbles vibration can be seen. My god such details.
EPIC!
This video deserves standing ovation! What a creation. Mesmerizing
I love it. Very artistic. Well done.
Truly piece of art! ❤️
